   <body>
      <context>You can create project status options to set the current implementation stage or state of a project in its life cycle.</context>
      <ol>
         <li href="../../../Warehouse/Task_Warehouse/ProjplanNav.dita#task-1465/ProPlanNav">
            <p/>
         </li>
         <li>
            <p>Click  <uicontrol>More</uicontrol>, and then click<uicontrol> Status and Attributes</uicontrol>.</p>
            <p>The <uicontrol>STATUS and ATTRIBUTES</uicontrol> list page is displayed.</p>
         </li>
         <li>
            <p>In the<uicontrol> STATUS LIST</uicontrol>section, click <uicontrol>Add</uicontrol>.</p>
            <p>The <uicontrol>New Status List</uicontrol> dialog box is displayed.</p>
         </li>
         <li>
            <p>In the <uicontrol>Status</uicontrol> name box, type the name of the status.</p>
         </li>
         <li>
            <p>Select the <uicontrol>ActivationStatus</uicontrol> check box to enable the availability of the status.</p>
         </li>
         <li>
            <p>Click <uicontrol>Save</uicontrol>.</p>
            <p>The <uicontrol>STATUS LIST</uicontrol>is updated with the new status.<p>The status is now available for selection in the <uicontrol>NEW PROJECT</uicontrol> and<uicontrol>EDIT PROJECT</uicontrol> pages.</p>
            </p>
         </li>
      </ol>
